Package uber

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Driver
    Driver for Uber
    Location
    Location contains an X and Y coordinate Classes keep track of their Location instead of a Grid keeping track of them
    Passenger  
    Title
    Car Title contains legal information about a car Not currently used for anything, just more identifying information about Driver
    Trip
    Trip contains all relevant information about a single Uber trip Allows for information to be easily passed Different Uber trips can extend this and overwrite distance calculation methods
    UberApp
    UberApp connects the various methods and classes of the package into one cohesive program Represents the overall app connecting the Drivers and Passengers
    UberIO
    Controls I/O for the Uber program Uses JSON Contains warning because of json.simple's lack of generics and use of raw types
    UberRunner
    Main method that runs entire program
    User
    User of Uber is an abstract parent of Passenger and Driver
    UsersList
    UsersList is an enclosing class for Lists of Passenger and Driver Primarily implemented so initializer could pass both lists, also used for some of UberRunner's methods
